                <head>143. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On May 6, 1954, President <persName corresp="#p_SGA1">Somoza</persName> called a
                    press conference to announce that a large arms cache had been discovered on
                    Nicaragua’s Pacific Coast after an unidentified submarine had been seen.
                    According to <persName>Piero Gleijeses</persName> in <hi rend="italic">Shattered
                        Hope</hi>:</p>
                <p>“For anyone who couldn’t divine the source of the weapons and the nationality of
                    the submarine, a clue was obligingly provided: the arms Oxz; were stamped with a
                    hammer and sickle.’ The weapons had, in fact, been planted by the <gloss
                        target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>, with <persName corresp="#p_SGA1"
                        >Somoza</persName>’s enthusiastic complicity. The ploy, however, was too
                    crude to have much value as propaganda and received only limited attention at
                    the time.” (page 294)</p>
            </div>
